<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,395]" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,225,251]" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Note</emphasis>
: The 
<typeStatus box="[323,371,225,251]" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1904" box="[469,722,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Hyperaeschra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis box="[469,722,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Hyperaeschra collaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moore, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[1059,1436,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Allodonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkima">
<emphasis box="[1059,1264,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Allodonta sikkima</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." box="[1279,1428,225,251]" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 198" refId="ref12269" refString="Moore, F. (1879) Heterocera. In: Hewitson, W. C. &amp; Moore, F. (Ed.), Descriptions of new Indian lepidopterous insects from the collection of the late Mr. W. S. Atkinson, M. A., F. I. S. &amp; c. Part 1. Asiatic Society of Bengal, Calcutta and Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. 1 - 198." type="book chapter" year="1879">Moore, 1879</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(now valid as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chandra et al." authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[316,548,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Hexafrenum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkima">
<emphasis box="[316,548,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Hexafrenum sikkima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Savela, M." box="[604,766,261,287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" refId="ref12704" refString="Savela, M. (2019) FUNET. Avaialble from: http: // ftp. funet. fi / pub / sci / bio / life / insecta / lepidoptera (last accessed on 8 August 2019)" type="url" year="2019">Savela (2019)</bibRefCitation>
. Further investigations revealed that 
<bibRefCitation author="Schintlmeister, A." box="[1191,1436,261,287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" refId="ref12906" refString="Schintlmeister, A. (2013) Notodontidae &amp; Oenosandridae (Lepidoptera). In: World Catalogue of Insects. Vol. 11. Brill, Leiden, 605 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004259188" type="book" year="2013">Schintlmeister (2013)</bibRefCitation>
erected 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Swinhoe" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[238,467,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Hexafrenum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis box="[238,467,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">Hexafrenum collaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species, therefore it is now being added to the existing list of Indian 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, previous distributions were only from NE 
<collectingCountry box="[865,926,333,359]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="129">India</collectingCountry>
. Our primary data adds Western and Central Himalayan distribution for the species.
</paragraph>
